Description: Fragment of oval, asymmetric handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay coarse orange-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '2'. Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 32, 29, 116, 8 or 173, 22. A common stamp, perhaps Rhodian.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1520)
